The paper is about machine comprehension, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the computer science category. The paper proposes a novel neural network architecture for machine reading task, which involves encoding and matching of query and passage. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related tasks. The paper also uses skip-gram model for embedding and memory network for matching, which are techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions achieving state-of-the-art results on TriviaQA dataset, which is a task related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and question answering. Finally, the paper uses neural networks, which are also used in neural engineering (cs.NE).
